N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 160.5 - Temporary license

State Regulations

An applicant who meets all requirements of licensure but
for the passage of a written and/or practical examination may make application
for a temporary license. Such temporary license shall expire six months from
issuance. A second temporary license will not be issued without proof that the
applicant has passed the written or practical examination. Notes
